  "question_id": "1672341a-9240-45b8-b1f1-4407773a8c8f",
  "short_text": "Print N Times",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints the number **0** `N` times on `N` lines.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` lines containing an integer **0** on each line.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\n\n* The number **0** should be printed **4** times.\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n0\n0\n0\n0\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "8403f5e6-869e-49ce-883d-94c622673216",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\ncounter = 0\n\nwhile counter < number:\n    print(0)\n    counter = counter + 1",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
